# {{lb|en|dated}} A [[female]] [[poet]].

====Usage notes====
{{m|en|poetess|Poetess}} is rare in contemporary usage according to which both sexes are known normally as {{m|en|poet|poets}}. The Latin term for a female poet was {{m|la|poētria}}, derived from the {{cog|grc|ποιήτρια}}, which still means “female poet” in Modern Greek. “Female poet” is the more usual modern translation where the gendered form in the original language is preserved.

